{"parentUuid":"3aebb044-b4db-4ca9-afa7-28c95386774e","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"e117d56d-29de-4df3-8e3a-07358c407d0d","agentId":"a25edca7176cfc694","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0113N26WGvRr358gYHPSQJDe","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"dynamic benchmark contamination resistant freshness held-out canary string functional benchmark\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Recent Advances in Large Langauge Model Benchmarks against Data Contamination: From Static to Dynamic Evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2502.17521v1\"},{\"title\":\"Recent Advances in Large Langauge Model Benchmarks against Data Contamination: From Static to Dynamic Evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.17521\"},{\"title\":\"How Can I Publish My LLM Benchmark Without Giving the ...\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.18102\"},{\"title\":\"The Problem with Benchmark Contamination in AI\",\"url\":\"https://www.deeplearning.ai/the-batch/the-problem-with-benchmark-contamination-in-ai/\"},{\"title\":\"Towards Contamination Resistant Benchmarks\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.08389\"},{\"title\":\"Language model benchmark - Wikipedia\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Language_model_benchmark\"},{\"title\":\"VeRA: Verified Reasoning Data Augmentation at Scale\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.13217\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - tongye98/Awesome-Code-Benchmark: A comprehensive code domain benchmark review of LLM researches. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/tongye98/Awesome-Code-Benchmark\"},{\"title\":\"Reward Modeling for Reinforcement Learning-Based LLM Reasoning: Design, Challenges, and Evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2602.09305\"},{\"title\":\"Search-Time Data Contamination\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2508.13180v1\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about these related concepts:\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n**Canary Strings**: Canary strings are deliberately crafted, unique tokens embedded within a dataset to serve as markers for data contamination. When a model's output unexpectedly includes these tokens, it strongly indicates that the model has memorized portions of its training data rather than learning to generalize.\n\n**Held-Out Data**: Held-out data prevents contamination. This approach involves keeping test data separate and not publishing it publicly, allowing for private evaluation.\n\n**Dynamic Benchmarks**: A key strategy to address contamination is to create a dynamic benchmark that receives continuous updates, with new test instances added after a model's training cutoff.\n\n**Contamination Resistant Benchmarks**: A contamination resistant benchmark should assess certain capabilities of LLMs, be dynamic and evolving over time to prevent contamination, ensure that contamination provides no advantage in model performance, while consistently assessing the same set of capabilities and maintaining the same level of task complexity to ensure fairness in evaluation over time.\n\n**Freshness**: As training corpora expand, evaluation integrity becomes increasingly fragile, as test items can appear in training data through direct inclusion, near-duplicates, or widespread online exposure.\n\nThese approaches work together to address the challenge of benchmark contamination in large language models by ensuring evaluation integrity.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"eb09ad13-bff6-4806-873b-0d02fff6f399","timestamp":"2026-06-21T05:15:03.588Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"dynamic benchmark contamination resistant freshness held-out canary string functional benchmark","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_016grM2HPnYL3Q5CFrkDxnUE","content":[{"title":"Recent Advances in Large Langauge Model Benchmarks against Data Contamination: From Static to Dynamic Evaluation","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2502.17521v1"},{"title":"Recent Advances in Large Langa