rk should assess certain capabilities of LLMs, be dynamic and evolving over time to prevent contamination, ensure that contamination provides no advantage in model performance, while consistently assessing the same set of capabilities and maintaining the same level of task complexity to ensure fairness in evaluation over time.\n\n**Freshness**: As training corpora expand, evaluation integrity becomes increasingly fragile, as test items can appear in training data through direct inclusion, near-duplicates, or widespread online exposure.\n\nThese approaches work together to address the challenge of benchmark contamination in large language models by ensuring evaluation integrity."],"durationSeconds":7.345620833000168,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3aebb044-b4db-4ca9-afa7-28c95386774e","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
